    "body": "I don't feel strongly either way, but for consideration - R doesn't seem to normalize weights by default, nor does numpy.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [3]: pd.Series([1, 2, 3]).mean(weights=[1, 1, 2])\r\nOut[3]: 0.75\r\n\r\nIn [4]: np.average([1, 2, 3], weights=[1, 1, 2])\r\nOut[4]: 2.25\r\n```\r\nR\r\n```r\r\n> weighted.mean(x=c(1, 2, 3), w=c(1, 1, 2))\r\n[1] 2.25\r\n```\r\n"
  },
